OL,3,CCommunities minister pledges #6.7
OL,4,Cmillion for homelessness prevention
OL,6,FCommunities minister Gordon Lyons has
OL,7,Fpledged #6.7 million of additional
OL,8,Ffunding for homelessness prevention.
OL,10,FMr Lyons said the government has to
OL,11,F"make the strategic shift" towards
OL,12,Fprevention which he called a "positive
OL,13,Fstep in the right direction".
OL,15,FDuring the period from October 2023 to
OL,16,FMarch 2024, there was a total of 8,452
OL,17,Fpeople in Northern Ireland presenting
OL,18,Fas homeless, according to the Housing
OL,19,FExecutive.
