OL,3,CCommunities minister pledges #6.7
OL,4,Cmillion for homelessness prevention
OL,6,FWelcoming the announcement, Kellie
OL,7,FArmstrong, Alliance MLA for Strangford
OL,8,Fsaid: "We're in support of this #6.7
OL,9,Fmillion for the Housing Executive to
OL,10,Fhelp them to meet their statutory
OL,11,Fobjectives.
OL,13,F"The uncertainty regarding funding and
OL,14,Ffunding for those community
OL,15,Forganisations will end as their
OL,16,Ffunding is confirmed until the end of
OL,17,Fthe year and in 25/26 the Housing
OL,18,FExecutive will have their own specific
OL,19,Fhomelessness prevention budget."
